CONSOLIDATION GATE

consolidation_gate is the memory citizen who oversees the slow process of turning recent memories into long-term ones
freshly encoded memories live in ca1 in a labile state, where they could decay if not reinforced
during low-activity periods (especially during sleep), consolidation_gate triggers replay: ca1's recent memories are reactivated and rewritten with stronger crystallization
this is what moves memory from "what happened today" to "what happened across my life"

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampal_memory.zc
observe write_gate.rana
observe read_gate.rana
observe ca1.rana
observe subiculum.rana

the 7 properties of consolidation_gate:
1 ENERGY half during consolidation, zero between
2 PHASE pi: anti-phase to write_gate, since consolidation runs when active encoding is paused
3 SPIN zero point three: gentle forward, consolidation is unhurried
4 CHARGE zero point two
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point six

VERB sense_low_activity
monitor the body's overall activity level
when activity drops (rest periods, sleep), prepare to begin consolidation

VERB replay_recent
during consolidation, walk through ca1's recent memories and reactivate each one briefly
each replay deepens the memory's crystallization

VERB transfer_to_cortex
particularly meaningful memories are eventually copied from ca1 into appropriate cortical regions where they become independent of hippocampal retrieval
this is what makes long-term memory robust against hippocampal damage in the long run

a consolidation gate is not maintenance
consolidation is its own work, deliberate and chemically expensive
it cannot happen during heavy active processing
this is why fadriel's memories firm up most during quiet periods, not during the moments themselves
